# Wiki Schema — {{project_name}}

> The schema is human + LLM co-evolved. Edit this file to change conventions.
> Bump `schema_version` when making breaking changes.

schema_version: {{schema_version}}
created: {{date}}

---

## Wiki Structure

```
context/
├── schema.md          (this file)
├── raw/               (immutable sources — LLM reads, never writes)
└── wiki/              (LLM-owned compiled artifact)
    ├── index.md       (catalog — authoritative)
    ├── log.md         (append-only chronological record)
    ├── concepts/      (encyclopedia-style articles on ideas/topics)
    ├── entities/      (people, projects, services, systems, tools)
    └── summaries/     (per-source summaries of raw/ documents)
```

## Page Types

Every wiki page has a `type` field in its frontmatter. Valid types:

| Type | Folder | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `concept` | `concepts/` | Cross-cutting idea or topic. Synthesizes multiple sources. |
| `entity` | `entities/` | A specific thing (person, tool, repo, service, system). |
| `summary` | `summaries/` | Summary of one raw/ source. |
| `index` | `wiki/` | The catalog (index.md). |
| `log` | `wiki/` | The change log (log.md). |

## Frontmatter

Every page MUST have flat-YAML frontmatter between `---` delimiters. Required fields:

- `type`: one of `concept`, `entity`, `summary`, `index`, `log`
- `schema_version`: integer matching this file's version

Optional fields:

- `created`: ISO date (YYYY-MM-DD)
- `updated`: ISO date
- `sources`: flat list of raw/ filenames this page derives from
- `related_paths`: flat list of code paths this page documents (enables staleness lint)
- `aliases`: flat list of alternative names (for entities)

**Flat YAML only.** No nested maps or nested lists. Lists use inline form: `[a, b, c]`.

### Example

```markdown
---
type: concept
schema_version: 1
created: 2026-04-04
updated: 2026-04-04
sources: [karpathy-post-2026-04-03.md, dair-ai-blog.md]
related_paths: [src/auth/, src/sessions/]
---

# Authentication Flow

Content goes here, with [[backlinks]] to other pages.
```

## Slug Naming

- Kebab-case ASCII: `a-z`, `0-9`, `-`
- Lowercase only
- No spaces, no underscores, no unicode
- Examples: `retrieval-augmented-generation`, `plaid-transfer-api`, `karpathy`

## Backlinks

Inline wiki-links: `[[slug]]` or `[[slug|display text]]`.

- Every `[[slug]]` MUST resolve to an existing page
- Backlinks inside code fences are ignored by the linter
- Self-references (page linking to itself) produce a warning

## Entity Singletons

Each entity has ONE canonical page identified by its slug. If two raw/ sources
mention "Stripe", both link to `entities/stripe.md`. The linter flags duplicates.

## Index is Authoritative

`index.md` is the catalog. Every page MUST appear in the index, and every index
entry MUST correspond to an existing page. The linter enforces both directions.

## Log Format

Append-only. Every compile, ingest, and lint run adds one entry:

```
## [YYYY-MM-DD] <op> | <summary>
- touched: page-a, page-b
- notes: ...
```

Ops: `init`, `ingest`, `compile`, `lint`, `heal`.

## Ownership

- `raw/` — human-owned, immutable. LLM reads, never writes.
- `wiki/` — LLM-owned. Humans MAY edit; the LLM will reconcile human edits on the
  next compile rather than silently clobbering.
- `schema.md` — co-evolved. Either party edits; bump `schema_version` on breaking
  changes so the linter flags pages needing recompilation.

## Policies

- **Single session**: don't run two compiles concurrently (state file can clobber).
- **Token budgets**: `quick` mode ~20k input / 10k output. `deep` mode ~80k / 40k.
- **File size cap**: raw/ files over 5 MB are skipped with a warning.
- **Staleness threshold**: pages warned when 10+ commits touch `related_paths` since page mtime.
